@TITLE "MMUPLAY(1)ĀmanualĀpage"
 @{" " link "'#toc'/MAIN"}Table of Contents

 @{" " link "'#toc0'/MAIN"}Name mmuplay - Simple console module player @{" " link "'#toc1'/MAIN"}Synopsis @{"b"}mmuplay@{"ub"} [@{"i"}generaloptions@{"ui"}] [@{"i"}deviceoptions@{"ui"}] [@{"i"}qualityoptions@{"ui"}] [@{"i"}otheroptions@{"ui"}] [@{"i"}MODFILE...@{"ui"}] @{" " link "'#toc2'/MAIN"}Description @{"b"}mmuplay@{"ub"} is a simple module player, it plays sequence of @{"i"}MODFILE@{"ui"}s, if no @{"i"}MODFILE@{"ui"}s is given then module will be loaded from standard input. If readline support is present and module is not loaded from standard input, then playback can be controlled from the keyboard. 

@{"b"}mmuplay@{"ub"} is part of the MikMod Utilities package, and uses MikMod Sound Library to load and play modules. @{" " link "'#toc3'/MAIN"}Exit Status @{"b"}mmuplay@{"ub"} uses standard exit status, as defined in sysexits.h. See a description of all exit codes in @{" " link "'mmu.1'/MAIN"}@{"b"}mmu@{"ub"}(1) . @{" " link "'#toc4'/MAIN"}General Options See a description of all general options in @{" " link "'mmu.1'/MAIN"}@{"b"}mmu@{"ub"}(1) . @{" " link "'#toc5'/MAIN"}Device Options @{"b"}-d, --dev=@{"ub"}@{"i"}DEVNO@{"ui"} Specify output device number which will be used for sound playback. Zero number means device autodetection, this is the default. Specify @{"b"}help@{"ub"} as argument to get a list of all possible device numbers. @{"b"}-a, --params=@{"ub"}@{"i"}PARAMS@{"ui"} Specify output device parameters. See section DRIVER PARAMETERS of libmikmod README file, to get information about all possible device parameters. @{" " link "'#toc6'/MAIN"}Quality Options @{"b"}-r, --mixfreq=@{"ub"}@{"i"}RATE@{"ui"} Sound playback frequency, in hertz. High values yield high sound quality, but need more computing power than lower values. The default value is 44100 Hz, which is compact disc quality. Other common values are 22100 Hz (radio quality), 11025 Hz (phone quality), and 8000 Hz (mu-law quality). @{"b"}-s, --stereo@{"ub"} Select stereo sound. This is the default. @{"b"}-m, --mono@{"ub"} Select mono sound. @{"b"}-1, --16bit@{"ub"} Select 16 bit sound mode. This mode yields better sound quality, but needs twice more mixing time, in comparison with 8 bit sound mode. The default is to use 16 bit sound mode. @{"b"}-8, --8bit@{"ub"} Select 8 bit sound mode. @{"b"}-h, --hqmixer@{"ub"} Select the high-quality software mixer. This mode yields better sound quality, but needs more mixing time. @{"b"}-H, --nohqmixer@{"ub"} Disable high-quality software mixer. This is the default. @{"b"}-p, --pansep=@{"ub"}@{"i"}PANSEP@{"ui"} Set stereo channels separation to @{"i"}PANSEP@{"ui"}. Allowed values range from 0 (no separation, thus mono sound) to 128 (full channel separation). The default value is 128. @{"b"}-e, --reverb=@{"ub"}@{"i"}REVERB@{"ui"} Set amount of sound reverberation to @{"i"}REVERB@{"ui"}. Allowed values range from 0 (no reverberation) to 15 (a rough estimate for chaos...). The default value is 0. @{"b"}-i, --interp@{"ub"} Enable the interpolated mixers. Interpolated mixing gives better sound but takes a bit more time than standard mixing. If the MikMod library is built with the high quality mixer, interpolated mixing is always enabled, regardless of this option. @{"b"}-I, --nointerp@{"ub"} Disable the interpolated mixers. @{"b"}-u, --surround@{"ub"} Enable the surround mixers. Since surround mixing works only for stereo sound, this option has no effect if the sound playback is in mono. @{"b"}-U, --nosurround@{"ub"} Disable the surround mixers. @{"b"}-n, --maxchan=@{"ub"}@{"i"}MAXCH@{"ui"} The maximum number of channels the song is allowed to request from the mixer. @{" " link "'#toc7'/MAIN"}Other Options @{"b"}-v, --volume=@{"ub"}@{"i"}VOLUME@{"ui"} Set sound volume to @{"i"}VOLUME@{"ui"}. Allowed values range from 0 to 128. The default value is 128. @{"b"}--reverse@{"ub"} Exchange the left and right stereo channels. @{"b"}-c, --curious@{"ub"} Enable curiosity level. If this option is given the following things occur: pattern positions occurring after the "end of song" marker in S3M and IT modules are loaded, and the end of song is set to the last position; hidden extra patterns are searched in MOD modules, and if found, played after the last "official" pattern; MED modules with synthsounds are loaded without causing the MMERR_MED_SYNTHSAMPLES, and synthsounds are mapped to an empty sample. @{"b"}-S, --skip=@{"ub"}@{"i"}NUMBER@{"ui"} Skip @{"i"}NUMBER@{"ui"} patterns from beginning of each module. @{"b"}-C, --count=@{"ub"}@{"i"}NUMBER@{"ui"} Process only @{"i"}NUMBER@{"ui"} patterns of each module. @{"b"}-o, --loop=@{"ub"}@{"i"}NUMBER@{"ui"} Loop modules @{"i"}NUMBER@{"ui"} times, 0 (zero) means loop forever. @{"b"}-l, --label=@{"ub"}@{"i"}LABEL@{"ui"} Use @{"i"}LABEL@{"ui"} as file name for standard input. @{"b"}-T, --filesfrom=@{"ub"}@{"i"}FILE@{"ui"} Read module list from @{"i"}FILE@{"ui"}. Each line of @{"i"}FILE@{"ui"} is a module file name. Empty lines and lines starting with # are ignored. If @{"i"}FILE@{"ui"} is -, then list will be loaded from standard input. @{"b"}-X, --filesfromcmd=@{"ub"}@{"i"}COMMAND@{"ui"} Read module list from output of @{"i"}COMMAND@{"ui"}. The @{"i"}COMMAND@{"ui"} will be passed to the shell (/bin/sh -c). Each line of output is a module file name. Empty lines and lines starting with # are ignored. @{"b"}--nocontrol@{"ub"} Disable control from the console. @{"b"}-t, --title@{"ub"} Display module title instead of file name. @{"b"}-q, --quiet@{"ub"} Do not write anything to standard output. @{" " link "'#toc8'/MAIN"}Console Control Console control is enabled if readline support is present (this is configured at compile-time) and module is not loaded from standard input and no @{"b"}--nocontrol@{"ub"} option is given. 

The following keys are recognized: f seek forward to the next position b seek backward to the previous position space toggle pause n jump to the next song p jump to the previous song + increase volume - decrease volume i print module info c print module comment u list module instruments s list module samples h print kyes help q quit @{" " link "'#toc9'/MAIN"}Notes Some defaults of @{"i"}quality options@{"ui"} can be changed at compile-time. To get information about compile-time configuration use @{"b"}mmu --version@{"ub"} command. @{" " link "'#toc10'/MAIN"}Bugs If you found any, please let me known. @{" " link "'#toc11'/MAIN"}Author Konstantin Korikov <lostclus@ua.fm> @{" " link "'#toc12'/MAIN"}See Also @{" " link "'mmu.1'/MAIN"}@{"b"}mmu(1) ,@{"ub"} @{" " link "'mikmod.guide/MAIN"}@{"b"}mikmod(1)@{"ub"} 


